    ("Can callers tell they are speaking to an AI receptionist?", "Modern AI receptionists are sophisticated enough that many callers cannot reliably distinguish them from human agents during a standard intake call. Voice synthesis technology has improved to the point where cadence, tone, and conversational flow are natural. That said, many law firms choose to be transparent with callers — disclosing early in the call that they are speaking with an AI assistant. Research suggests this transparency does not significantly reduce caller satisfaction and may actually increase trust by setting appropriate expectations."),
